DTR Hangup mod for Anchor MK XII   by Barry A. Cole  30 JAN 1985
----------------------------------------------------------------
Thió wilì causå á fulì reseô wheî DTÒ ió broughô high(-12v)®  Thió 
followó thå standarä definitioî oæ RS23² anä makeó thå Anchoò 
compatiblå witè thå Hayeó Smartmodeí foò usagå withiî "BYE.COM".

     Installation:

1)Open the modem case using a wide blade screwdriver.  Pry the top
  separate from the bottom.

2)Soldeò thå bandeä enä oæ á smalì switchinç diodå sucè aó 1N91´ oò 
  1N414¸ tï thå RS23² connectoò piî 20®  Keeð thå leaä lonç anä inserô 
  iî á piecå oæ sleevinç strippeä froí á wire®  Lookinç froí wherå thå 
  ribboî cablå enteró thå board¬ thió ió thå centeò oæ thå · pinó iî 
  thå 2nä ro÷ from the outside of the case.

3)Soldeò thå otheò enä oæ thå diodå tï á piecå oæ wire®  Slidå sleevinç 
  over the exposed diode lead for insulation.

4)Solder the other end of the wire to the plus(+) side of capacitor C48.
  This was in the farthest corner of mine.  On newer boards, it is near
  the center of the board.

